{"title":"Preface","markdown":{"headingText":"Preface","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":["unnumbered"],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\nWelcome to the **Namma Cloud Standard Operating Procedures (SOP) Book** — a comprehensive guide for our admin team responsible for building, managing, and maintaining our private cloud data center infrastructure.\n\n## Who Is This Book For?\n\nThis book is written for every member of the Namma Cloud Admin Team — from team leads with deep technical knowledge to team members who are learning new skills every day. Whether you are:\n\n- **Transporting servers** from one location to the data center\n- **Fitting servers** into racks and ensuring proper alignment\n- **Connecting power and network** cables\n- **Verifying server health** after installation\n- **Learning new concepts** about cloud infrastructure\n\n...this book has clear, step-by-step procedures for you.\n\n## Why This Book Exists\n\nSetting up a private cloud data center is a complex, multi-layered effort. Our team has already faced real challenges:\n\n- A server was damaged during transportation due to inadequate packaging\n- Assembled (non-branded) servers did not fit well into standard racks\n- Alignment issues were discovered during rack fitting\n\nEach of these incidents taught us something valuable. This book captures those lessons and turns them into **repeatable, reliable processes** so that we never make the same mistake twice.\n\n## How to Use This Book\n\n| Part | What You'll Find |\n|------|-----------------|\n| **Vision & Foundations** | Our mission, principles, and team structure |\n| **Standard Operating Procedures** | Step-by-step guides for every physical task |\n| **Quality & Governance** | Maker-Checker processes, RCA, and issue tracking |\n| **Learning & Technology** | Upskilling modules and Namma DSL integration |\n| **Appendices** | Ready-to-use checklists, templates, and glossary |\n\n: Book Structure Overview {.striped}\n\n## A Living Document\n\nThis book is not static. As we learn, as we encounter new challenges, and as our infrastructure grows, this book will evolve. Every team member is encouraged to:\n\n1. **Flag gaps** — If something is missing, raise it\n2. **Suggest improvements** — If a process can be better, propose changes\n3. **Document incidents** — Every issue is a learning opportunity\n4. **Use AI tools** — Leverage AI to understand, verify, and improve\n\n> *\"We are building not just a data center, but a culture of excellence, curiosity, and continuous learning.\"*\n\n---\n\n**Let's build something extraordinary together.**\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"ht